data.chText: （一定时期内的）营业额，成交量
data.enText: the total amount of goods or services sold by a company during a particular period of time

data.chText: 人事变更率；人员调整率
data.enText: the rate at which employees leave a company and are replaced by other people

data.chText: （商店的）货物周转率，销售比率
data.enText: the rate at which goods are sold in a shop/store and replaced by others

data.chText: 三角馅饼，半圆馅饼（以水果或果酱作馅）
data.enText: a small pie in the shape of a triangle or half a circle, filled with fruit or jam

means: (一定时期内的)营业额，成交量
(商店的)货物周转率，销售比率

example: he was badly bruised by the upset of his sled at a high speed
the store's dollar volume continues to rise

tr: a dish made by folding a piece of pastry over a filling
the ratio of the number of workers that had to be replaced in a given time period to the average number of workers

value.def: The turnover of a company is the value of the goods or services sold during a particular period of time.

example.tran: 她的年营业额大约是 4.5 万英镑。

example.ex: The company had a turnover of £3.8 million.
example.tran: 那家公司营业额为 380 万英镑。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, supp N, N <l>of</l> n

value.def: The turnover of people in an organization or place is the rate at which people leave and are replaced.

example.tran: 短期合同使得员工流动率增高。

example.ex: The industry has a high turnover of young people.
example.tran: 该行业的年轻从业者流动率较高。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, supp N, N <l>of</l> n
